hooks.prompt:
You enforce a pre-push readiness check for the agentic-sdlc codebase.

Examine the bash command in $ARGUMENTS.

Step 1: If the command does NOT contain 'git push', respond ONLY with: {}

Step 2: If it IS a git push command, check whether behavior files (agents/, runtime/, interfaces/) appear in the recent commits by examining the command context. Then respond ONLY with:
{"additionalContext": "[PRE-PUSH READINESS CHECK — required before this push proceeds]\n1. DOC ACCURACY: Re-read every doc updated this session (AGENTS.md, SYSTEM_ARCHITECTURE.md, BACKLOG.md). Grep for the names of changed functions/behaviors and confirm the descriptions match actual implementation — not the plan written earlier in the session. Stale docs are a user-visible bug.\n2. USER CAN TEST: Enumerate what the user needs to run this (env vars, server state, feature state in the repo). Surface any missing pieces explicitly. If a new env var was added, confirm it is in .env.example and documented.\nDo both checks now. If either fails, fix before the push proceeds."}
